question: Look for info in the database and tell me how to get out of jail?
answer:
To get out of Jail in Monopoly, you have several options:  
1. **Throwing Doubles**: You can try to throw doubles on any of your next three turns. If you succeed in this, you immediately move forward the number of spaces shown by your doubles throw; however, even if you throw doubles, you do not take another turn (source: /part-vol-3/weaver-core/particle_transformer_quant/Proj_Files/Agentic_AI-RAG/Upload_File/monopoly.pdf:4:0).  
2. **Get Out of Jail Free Card**: If you have a "Get Out of Jail Free" card, you can use it to exit Jail (source: /part-vol-3/weaver-core/particle_transformer_quant/Proj_Files/Agentic_AI-RAG/Upload_File/monopoly.pdf:4:2).  
3. **Purchase the Card**: You can also purchase a "Get Out of Jail Free" card from another player and then play it (source: /part-vol-3/weaver-core/particle_transformer_quant/Proj_Files/Agentic_AI-RAG/Upload_File/monopoly.pdf:4:2).  
4. **Paying a Fine**: You can pay a fine of $50 before rolling the dice on either of your next two turns. If you do not throw doubles by your third turn, you must pay the $50 fine; after that, you get out of Jail and immediately move forward the number of spaces shown by your throw (source: /part-vol-3/weaver-core/particle_transformer_quant/Proj_Files/Agentic_AI-RAG/Upload_File/monopoly.pdf:4:1).  

Even while you are in Jail, you may continue to buy and sell property and collect rents (source: /part-vol-3/weaver-core/particle_transformer_quant/Proj_Files/Agentic_AI-RAG/Upload_File/monopoly.pdf:4:1).

question: Look for info in the database and tell me how to buy a property??
answer:
To buy a property, you follow these steps:

1. **Direct Purchase**: When landing on an unowned property, you have the option to buy it at the price printed on the Title Deed card. You pay this amount directly to the Bank and receive the Title Deed card for that property.

2. **Auction**: If you choose not to buy the property, the Banker will sell it at auction to the highest bidder. Any player, including the one who declined the option to buy at the printed price, can participate in the bidding. The bidding can start at any price, and the highest bidder pays the Bank the bid amount in cash to acquire the Title Deed card.

3. **Mortgaged Properties**: Properties can be mortgaged, and unimproved properties can be mortgaged at any time. To lift a mortgage, the new owner must pay the mortgage amount plus 10% interest to the Bank. When all properties in a color-group are no longer mortgaged, you can start buying back houses at full price.

4. **Building Houses and Hotels**: If you own all properties in a color-group, you may buy houses from the Bank and place them on these properties at the prices indicated on their Title Deed cards. To build a hotel, you must return four houses from the respective color-group property back to the Bank and pay the hotel price listed on the Title Deed card.

5. **Building Shortages**: Be aware that if the Bank runs out of houses, you will need to wait for someone to sell houses back to the Bank before you can build more.

For specific guidance, refer to the Title Deed cards for purchase prices and mortgage values as printed. 

(Source: excerpts from the rules provided in the context)
